"Bonnefille R., Potts R., Chalié F., Jolly D., Peyron O.","High-resolution vegetation and climate change associated with Pliocene Australopithecus afarensis",2004,"Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America","101","33",,"12125","12129",,,10.1073/pnas.0401709101,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-4344608501&partnerID=40&md5=d84d87e208a784f0469016686e0237fe","Ctr. Europ. de Rech./d'Enseignement, Unité Mixte de Recherche 6635, Ctr. Natl. de la Rech. Scientifique, B.P. 80, 13545 Aix-en-Provence Cedex 04, France; Human Origins Program, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, DC 20560-0112, United States; Institut des Sciences de l'Evolution, Unité Mixte de Recherche, Université Montpellier II, F-34095 Montpellier Cedex 05, France; Laboratoire de Chronoécologie, Unité Mixte de Recherche 6565, Univ. de Franche Comté, 25030 Besançon, France","Bonnefille, R., Ctr. Europ. de Rech./d'Enseignement, Unité Mixte de Recherche 6635, Ctr. Natl. de la Rech. Scientifique, B.P. 80, 13545 Aix-en-Provence Cedex 04, France; Potts, R., Human Origins Program, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, DC 20560-0112, United States; Chalié, F., Ctr. Europ. de Rech./d'Enseignement, Unité Mixte de Recherche 6635, Ctr. Natl. de la Rech. Scientifique, B.P. 80, 13545 Aix-en-Provence Cedex 04, France; Jolly, D., Institut des Sciences de l'Evolution, Unité Mixte de Recherche, Université Montpellier II, F-34095 Montpellier Cedex 05, France; Peyron, O., Laboratoire de Chronoécologie, Unité Mixte de Recherche 6565, Univ. de Franche Comté, 25030 Besançon, France","Plio-Pleistocene global climate change is believed to have had an important influence on local habitats and early human evolution in Africa. Responses of hominin lineages to climate change have been difficult to test, however, because this procedure requires well documented evidence for connections between global climate and hominin environment. Through high-resolution pollen data from Hadar, Ethiopia, we show that the hominin Australopithecus afarensis accommodated to substantial environmental variability between 3.4 and 2.9 million years ago. A large biome shift, up to 5°C cooling, and a 200- to 300-mm/yr rainfall increase occurred just before 3.3 million years ago, which is consistent with a global marine δ18O isotopic shift.",,"rain; Africa; article; biome; climate change; Colinus; environmental temperature; Ethiopia; evolution; global climate; hominid; pliocene; pollen; priority journal; vegetation; Animals; Climate; Environment; Ethiopia; Evolution; Fossils; Hominidae; Humans; Plants; Pollen; Time Factors; Australopithecus afarensis; Colinus; Hominidae",,,,,,"Vrba, E.S., Denton, G.H., Partridge, T.C., Burckle, L.H., (1995) Paleoclimate and Evolution, with Emphasis on Human Origins, , Yale Univ. Press, New Haven, CT; DeMenocal, P.B., (1995) Science, 270, pp. 53-59; Potts, R., (1998) Yrb. Phys. Anthropol., 41, pp. 93-136; WoldeGabriel, G., White, T.D., Suwa, G., Renne, P., De Heinzelin, J., Hart, W.K., Heiken, G., (1994) Nature, 371, pp. 330-333; Behrensmeyer, A.K., Todd, N.E., Potts, R., McBrinn, G.E., (1997) Science, 278, pp. 1589-1594; Bobe, R., Behrensmeyer, A.K., Chapman, R.E., (2002) J. Hum. Evol., 42, pp. 475-497; Johanson, D.C., Taieb, M., Coppens, Y., (1982) Am. J. Phys. Anthropol., 57, pp. 373-402; Kimbel, W.H., Johanson, D.C., Rak, Y., (1994) Nature, 368, pp. 449-451; Lockwood, C.A., Kimbel, W.H., Johanson, D.C., (2000) J. Hum. Evol., 39, pp. 23-55; Aronson, J., Taieb, M., (1981) AAAS Sel. Symp., 63, pp. 165-195; Bonnefille, R., Vincens, A., Buchet, G., (1987) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 60, pp. 249-281; Walter, R.C., Aronson, J.L., (1993) J. Hum. Evol., 25, pp. 229-240; Walter, R.C., (1994) Geology, 22, pp. 6-10; Schmitt, T.J., Nairn, A.E.M., (1984) Nature, 309, pp. 704-706; Renne, P.R., Walter, R.C., Verosub, K.L., Sweitzer, M., Aronson, J.L., (1993) Geophys.